OL,11,Ftheir families to support and identify
OL,12,Fany lessons that we can learn to
OL,13,Fimprove the care we deliver.
OL,15,F"For those incidents, the Trust has
OL,16,Faccepted responsibility and apologises
OL,17,Fto the patients involved for the
OL,18,Fdistress and injury caused. The
OL,19,Ffigures were drawn form a Freedom of
OL,20,FInformation (FOI) response issued by
