OL,6,FThe British Trauma Association leader
OL,7,Fcontinued: "Birth trauma wasn't talked
OL,8,Fabout at all until relatively
OL,9,Frecently. Many women tell us they were
OL,10,Fcompletely unaware of, for example,
OL,11,Fthe possibility of sustaining injuries
OL,12,Fas a result of birth. We think this is
OL,13,Fpartly because there is a widespread
OL,14,Fattitude that we shouldn't make
OL,15,Fpregnant women feel frightened of
OL,16,Flabour, but also because there is a
OL,17,Ftendency to trivialise and ignore
OL,18,Fwomen's health problems.
