OL,6,F"When women do develop trauma symptoms
OL,7,Fafter birth, they are often told by
OL,8,Fothers to 'move on' and to feel
OL,9,Fgrateful that they have a healthy
OL,10,Fbaby."
OL,12,FFirst-degree tears are small and skin-
OL,13,Fdeep. Second-degree tears are deeper
OL,14,Fand affect the muscle of your
OL,15,Fperineum. Third-degree tears also
OL,16,Finvolve the muscle that controls the
OL,17,Fanus, according to NHS inform.
